ARP obtains MAC and IP addresses within a network
ARP is used to determine whether a destination address is within a network or not
the ARP cache stores addresses
ARP is a layer 2 protocol on the OSI model
  Layer 2 is the datalink layer

Packet Tracer ARP Troubleshooting tip:
  You will be unable to use ARP protocol in packet tracer if you have not pinged devices to eachother at least once
